net.truelicense.v1

Class V1LicenseApplicationContext

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.truelicense.core.TrueLicenseApplicationContext<GenericCertificate>
      • net.truelicense.v1.V1LicenseApplicationContext
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    RepositoryContextProvider<GenericCertificate>, CodecProvider, CompressionProvider, LicenseApplicationContext, LicenseFactory, LicenseManagementAuthorizationProvider, CachePeriodProvider, ClassLoaderProvider, Clock, PasswordPolicyProvider, PasswordProtectionProvider<ObfuscatedString>, BiosProvider

    public class V1LicenseApplicationContext
extends TrueLicenseApplicationContext<GenericCertificate>
    The root context for applications which need to manage Version 1 (V1) format license keys. This class is provided to enable applications to generate, install, verify and uninstall license keys in the format for TrueLicense 1.X applications. Since TrueLicense 2.0, this format is obsolete and should not be used for new applications! Note that there is no compatibility between different format license keys.

    This class is immutable.

    Author:
    Christian Schlichtherle

      • pbeAlgorithm

        public final String pbeAlgorithm()
        Returns the name of the default Password Based Encryption (PBE) algorithm for the license key format. You can override this default value when configuring the PBE.

        The implementation in the class V1LicenseApplicationContext returns "PBEWithMD5AndDES". This was the only supported PBE algorithm in TrueLicense 1 and its not possible to use another one.

        Specified by:
        pbeAlgorithm in class TrueLicenseApplicationContext<GenericCertificate>
        See Also:
        EncryptionInjection.algorithm(java.lang.String)

      • storeType

        public final String storeType()
        Returns the name of the default key store type, for example "JCEKS" or "JKS". You can override this default value when configuring the key store based authentication.

        The implementation in the class V1LicenseApplicationContext returns "JKS".
